title: When Unexpected Things Happen to George
description: A newcomer to George O'Grady's local bar, the upper-class Dr. Neil Beck, loses a bet to George. Unable to come up with the cash on-the-spot, he gives George his dog, who he takes an immediate dislike to.

title: George Sees an Airplane
description: Driving Dr. Beck to his house in Conneticut, George sees what looks like a U.F.O. in the sky. He tries to convince the customers of his local bar that he saw it, only to have his sanity questioned.

title: George Goes on a Date: Part 1
description: George decides to ask out pet-shop owner Kathleen Rachowski out on a date, despite the fact that he's never been in a relationship in over 8 years.

title: George Goes on a Date: Part 2
description: Continuing on from the events from the previous episode, George's date with the pet store owner Kathleen is interrupted when he discovers his dog, Miles, has run away.

title: George Helps Sydney
description: The bar gets a new pool table and Sydney gets an opportunity to audition for a modeling agency. The day before her audition, George accidentally hits her in the nose with a billiard ball.

title: George Expresses Himself
description: George gets a chance to appear on a talk show, to respond to the stereotypes of cab drivers he feels is hurting all cabbies' careers.

title: George Destroys a Way of Life
George Loses His Thermos
description: George can't find his thermos, and to their dismay accuses his friends at the bar of stealing it from him.

title: George Looks Down the Wrong End of a .38
description: A criminal hijacks George's taxi as he and Dr. Beck are driving to the Moylan bar.

title: George Plays a Mean Pinball
description: After beating his girlfriend Kathleen at multiple games of pinball, George begins insisting to her that women are inferior to men,

title: George Lifts the Holy Spirit
description: Harry steals a truck which has a statue of Jesus in the cargo bed. George tries to help him return it to the church.

title: George Runs Into an Old Friend
George Gets Hoist by His Own Petard
George Gets Caught in the Middle
George Really Does It This Time
George Shoots Himself in the Foot
George Puts on a Happy Face
